https://blog.codinghorror.com/so-youd-like-to-send-some-email-through-code/
1. Make sure the computer sending the email has a Reverse PTR record (something your ISP has to configure for you)
2. Configure DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM) in your DNS and code (DKIM support at MTA level using dkim-milter and sendmail/exim4/postfix)
3. Set up a SPF / SenderID record in your DNS
check reply when sending test email to auth@verifier.port25.com

A record maps domain name to an IP address, PTR maps an IP address to a hostname

user@example.com
user@example.com, anotheruser@example.com
User <user@example.com>
User <user@example.com>, Another User <anotheruser@example.com>


